Non - Primitive Data Types

Non-primitive data types: The non-primitive data types include String. =>String name="John"
There is no limit non=primitive data type. 

String Data Type: String is a sequence(siikwıns-dizi,sira) of connected characters.
                  (Dize, bağlı karakterlerin bir dizisidir.)

String nameOfSchool = “Dade College”;
String characters = “12!?<”;
String characters = “1”;
If you tell java even it is single character, I wanna use String data type, Java accepts it. 

Note: Put the String value between double quotes. I am typing the code between
 the double quotes. It is must.For chars you will use single quotes, for String you will use double quotes. 
Note: There are other non-primitive data types, we will learn them later.

